==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Schoolship
<hw>School"ship`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A vessel employed
as a nautical training school, in which naval apprentices receive their
education at the expense of the state, and are trained for service as
sailors. Also, a vessel used as a reform school to which boys are
committed by the courts to be disciplined, and instructed as
mariners.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>School-teacher</ent>⟦br⟧
